just_use events.go

# label: ELEGANT
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Cross-domain wire types + event replay. Only GameSetup is exported; the
wire* structs are internal JSON plumbing that consumers never see directly
— they call CheckEvent / ParseMoveEvent / ReconstructBoard.

CheckEvent is the single entry point the Host (games package) calls:
feed it all prior payloads + the new payload; it reconstructs the board,
parses the move, and routes to the referee. Non-player-action events
(advance-turn, undo) return nil (no ruling needed).

ReconstructBoard is deterministic replay: first payload must be a
game_setup, subsequent player-action payloads apply stacks_to_remove /
stacks_to_add in order. This is how the host maintains no in-memory game
state — every ruling is recomputed from event_ids.
